        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50349",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There are no plans to do this, in large part due to the fact that the support required BC breaks in order to implement.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-04-23T13:44:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-04-23T13:44:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50350",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=g.schuster",
                        "name": "g.schuster",
                        "displayName": "Gabriel Schuster",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well, there could be a simple solution: make it dependent on a static variable.\r\nWhen the variable is set to TRUE it useses the BC-breaking correct $origMsgId, otherwise it behaves as currently expected.\r\nCurrently it is an undesirable situation where one has to copy _all_ adapters to his own lib just to override the translate() method with the fixed version whereas my suggested fix would be as simple as calling Zend_Translate::useFixForBug11173(TRUE);\r\n\r\nWithout fixing or copying all adapters one has to check in _every_ call to translate (with plurals) if the returned value is a string or an array.\r\nA real show-stopper for any new (bigger) project.\r\n\r\n\r\nImplementation code for the fix:\r\n\r\n117: protected $_translate = array();\r\n+    \r\n+    protected static $_useFixForBug11173 = FALSE;\r\n+    \r\n+    public static function useFixForBug11173($useFix = FALSE) {\r\n+        self::$_useFixForBug11173 = (bool)$useFix;\r\n+    }\r\n+    \r\n+    public static function getFixForBug11173() {\r\n+        return self::$_useFixForBug11173;\r\n+    }\r\n\r\n705: - $plural = null;\r\n705: + $plural            = NULL;\r\n+      $originalMessageId = $messageId;\r\n\r\n732: - return $this->translate($messageId, $this->_options['route'][$locale]);\r\n732: + return $this->translate(self::$_useFixForBug11173 ? $originalMessageId : $messageId, $this->_options['route'][$locale]);\r\n\r\n790: - return $this->translate($messageId, $this->_options['route'][$locale]);\r\n790: + return $this->translate(self::$_useFixForBug11173 ? $originalMessageId : $messageId, $this->_options['route'][$locale]);",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=g.schuster",
                        "name": "g.schuster",
                        "displayName": "Gabriel Schuster",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-04-23T14:07:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-04-23T14:07:22.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
